The failing test `Create_Post_InvalidModel_ReturnsView` in InstructorsControllerTests fails because when the model state is invalid, the controller calls `PopulateAssignedCourseData(instructor)`, which accesses `instructor.CourseAssignments.Select(c => c.CourseID)`. Since the instructor's `CourseAssignments` is null, it throws `ArgumentNullException`.

I need to initialize `CourseAssignments` on the instructor in the test:
```csharp
var instructor = new Instructor
{
    HireDate = DateTime.Parse("2023-01-15"),
    CourseAssignments = new List<CourseAssignment>()
};
```

This ensures the collection exists and won't throw when the controller tries to access it.

